   <refnamediv>
       <refname>hypg_pdf </refname>
               <refpurpose>hypergeometric probability distribution </refpurpose>
   </refnamediv>
 
        <refsynopsisdiv>
               <title>CALLING SEQUENCE</title>
               <synopsis>[pdf]=hypg_pdf(k,n,K,N)</synopsis>
        </refsynopsisdiv>
 
        <refsection>
           <title>PARAMETERS</title>
           <variablelist>
           <varlistentry>
 
           <term>Input</term>
 
<listitem><para>* <term>k,n,K,N</term> =  the parameters of the distibution (probability of k successes in n draws, without replacement,
from a finite population of size N that contains exactly K successes, or matrix of parameters with the same size (pxq)</para></listitem>
 
 
 
<listitem><para>&#160;</para></listitem>
 
           </varlistentry>
 
          <varlistentry>
 
          <term>Output</term>
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> pdf </term> =    (pxq) vector containing pdf for each x</para></listitem>
 
 
          </varlistentry>
          </variablelist>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
Calculates the hypergeometric pdf function where the hypergeometric distribution corresponds to the probability of having k elements belonging to a class of size K in a random draw of n elements chosen among N.
 
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>EXAMPLE</title>
              <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
p=hypg_pdf(5,15,20,30)
 
               ]]></programlisting>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>AUTHOR</title>
Eric Dubois 2002
